    "promptReady": "# Software Services Invoice Ontology\n\nA US-domestic B2B invoice document type used by software staffing and development companies to bill clients for engineering services, typically on a monthly billing cycle with time-and-materials or fixed-fee pricing.\n\n**Domain:** finance\n\n## Classes\n\n### Invoice\n\n**Properties:**\n- Invoice Number\n  Examples: INV-001\n- Invoice Issue Date\n  Examples: MM/DD/YYYY\n- Delivery Date\n  Examples: MM/DD/YYYY\n- Billing Period\n  Examples: Month 16 - Next Month 15\n- Contract Number / SOW Reference\n  Examples: SOW-XXXXXXXXX\n- Total Invoice Amount\n  Examples: $XX,XXX.XX\n- Invoice Currency\n  Examples: USD\n- Sales Tax Amount\n  Examples: 0.00 (sales tax exempt)\n- Sales Tax Exemption Note\n  Examples: Sales tax not collected --- out-of-state buyer with no nexus.\n- Foreign Currency Equivalent\n  Examples: n/a (USD-only invoice)\n- Exchange Rate\n  Examples: n/a (USD-only invoice)\n- Payment Method\n  Examples: ACH Bank Transfer, Wire Transfer\n- Payment Deadline / Terms\n  Examples: Net 30, by Contract\n- Place of Issue\n  Examples: San Francisco\n\n**Relations:**\n- relates to → Seller / Issuer\n- relates to → Buyer / Client\n- part of → Line Item\n- part of → Signature and Responsibility Block\n\n**Examples:**\n- Invoice INV-001\n\n### Seller / Issuer\n\n**Properties:**\n- Seller Name\n  Examples: EXAMPLE SOFTWARE SERVICES LLC\n- Seller Address\n  Examples: 100 Market St, Suite 500, San Francisco, CA 94105\n- Seller Tax Identification Number\n  Examples: EIN: XX-XXXXXXX\n- Seller Business Registration Number\n  Examples: Business Registration No.: XXXXXXXX\n- Seller Contact Information\n  Examples: +1-415-XXX-XXXX, invoicing@example.com\n\n**Relations:**\n- relates to → Seller Bank Account\n\n**Examples:**\n- Example Software Services LLC\n\n### Buyer / Client\n\n**Properties:**\n- Buyer Name\n  Examples: Acme Corp Inc.\n- Buyer Address\n  Examples: 100 Example Avenue, Demo City, CA 94000, USA\n- Buyer Tax Identification Number\n  Examples: EIN: XX-XXXXXXX\n\n**Examples:**\n- Acme Corp Inc.\n\n### Seller Bank Account\n\n**Properties:**\n- Bank Name\n  Examples: Example Bank, San Francisco, CA\n- IBAN\n  Examples: n/a (US domestic)\n- SWIFT / BIC Code\n  Examples: n/a (US domestic)\n- Routing Number / Account Number\n  Examples: Routing: 121XXXXXX, Account: XXXXXXXXX\n\n**Examples:**\n- Example Bank, San Francisco, CA\n\n### Line Item\n\n**Properties:**\n- Line Item Description\n  Examples: Software Engineering Services\n- Quantity\n  Examples: 21 days, 1.00\n- Unit Price / Rate\n  Examples: $XX.XX per hour\n- Line Item Amount\n  Examples: $X,XXX.XX\n- Employee / Contractor Reference\n  Examples: Engineer A (SOW-A)\n- Working Days\n  Examples: 21 days\n- Days Off / Leave Days\n  Examples: 0 days, 1 day\n- Hours Per Day\n  Examples: 8 hours per day\n- Billing Period\n  Examples: Month 16 - Next Month 15\n- Rebate / Discount\n  Examples: 0.00, 0%\n\n**Examples:**\n- Software Engineering Services - Engineer A - 21 days\n\n### Signature and Responsibility Block\n\n**Examples:**\n- Responsible person details, signature line, optional stamp/seal\n\n## Dimensions\n\n### Service Type\n\n### Billing Model\n\n### Invoice Direction\n\n### Document Language\n\n## Constraints\n\n- **Total Amount Calculation Rule** (Line Item Amount, Total Invoice Amount): Total must equal sum of all line item amounts; for time-based: hourly_rate × hours_per_day × working_days (e.g., $38.00 × 8 × 19 = $5,776.00 USD)\n- **Sales Tax Exemption Rule** (Sales Tax Amount, Sales Tax Exemption Note): Sales tax not collected; out-of-state buyer with no nexus in the seller's state.\n- **Foreign Currency Conversion Rule** (Foreign Currency Equivalent, Exchange Rate): Foreign-currency invoices must show USD equivalent at the Federal Reserve H.10 rate on the invoice date; for USD-only invoices, this rule is satisfied trivially."
  }
